WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.130 --> 00:00:05.260
In A Song of Ice and Fire, the Long Night
was a dark time thousands of years ago when

00:00:05.260 --> 00:00:10.559
winter lasted a generation. It’s said that
during this time, there was no daylight, and

00:00:10.559 --> 00:00:16.129
Others, riding dead horses and monstrous spiders, came from the North to destroy all living

00:00:16.129 --> 00:00:20.589
things. We know the Long Night happened in Westeros, but it also affected the Rhoyne,

00:00:20.589 --> 00:00:25.679
and the Further East, so it was probably
worldwide. Melisandre says the Long Night

00:00:25.679 --> 00:00:30.759
is coming again, bringing an apocalyptic “night that never ends”. It’s starting to

00:00:30.759 --> 00:00:37.759
look like she might be right. Melisandre
says the only hope is a hero named Azor Ahai.

00:00:37.899 --> 00:00:39.630
People all over the world of ice and fire

00:00:39.630 --> 00:00:44.360
have stories of the hero who ended the last
Long Night. The Northerners say the “last

00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:48.360
hero” joined with the children of the forest
and won the Battle for the Dawn against the

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:53.020
Others. Descendants of the Rhoynar say a
hero convinced their gods to bring back the

00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:58.810
day with a secret song. The YiTish say a
woman with a monkey’s tail restored the

00:00:58.810 --> 00:01:03.540
sun. The Asshai’i name this hero Azor Ahai, and prophesy their rebirth to save the world

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:09.020
once more. The names Hyrkoon the Hero, Yin Tar, Neferion, and Eldric Shadowchaser are

00:01:09.020 --> 00:01:13.549
also used. There’s also “the prince that
was promised”. Some people think the “prince

00:01:13.549 --> 00:01:17.530
that was promised” and Azor Ahai are separate figures, but there’s no good reason to think

00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:23.049
this. Melisandre, Aemon Targaryen, and George R. R. Martin himself all talk as though Azor

00:01:23.049 --> 00:01:26.639
Ahai and the “prince that was promised”
are the same thing, and no one in A Song

00:01:26.639 --> 00:01:30.659
of Ice and Fire has ever distinguished between the two. So “the prince that was promised”

00:01:30.659 --> 00:01:35.549
and Azor Ahai reborn appear to be the same person. The “stallion who mounts the world”

00:01:35.549 --> 00:01:40.729
may also be connected. He too is described as a “prince” , and is promised in prophecy.

00:01:40.729 --> 00:01:45.310
Given the blurry overlap and similarity of
these legends, it seems likely that they’re

00:01:45.310 --> 00:01:50.920
all about the same person, the hero who saved
the world from the Long Night, and is prophesied

00:01:50.920 --> 00:01:55.850
to return, to save the world once more. We’ll
call’m Azor Ahai because that’s the best

00:01:55.850 --> 00:02:02.439
known name and the easiest to say.
So what do we know about Azor Ahai? Melisandre

00:02:02.439 --> 00:02:07.109
says Azor Ahai is prophesied to be born beneath a “bleeding star”, “amidst salt and

00:02:07.109 --> 00:02:11.980
smoke”. We hear the same thing from Aemon Targaryen, from Benerro, the High red priest

00:02:11.980 --> 00:02:16.650
of Volantis, and from Marwyn the Mage, who says he doesn’t trust prophecy. Rhaegar

00:02:16.650 --> 00:02:20.790
Targaryen believed in these prophetic signs, and it seems likely that his wife Elia and

00:02:20.790 --> 00:02:26.280
some other family members did as well. We’re told many times by many people that the star,

00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:31.420
salt and smoke are signs of Azor Ahai, so
it seems almost certain that they truly are.

00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:37.000
According to Melisandre and Aemon, another sign is a red or burning sword, called Lightbringer,

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:42.110
which also appears in several legends. Sam Tarly suggests that the sword may simply be

00:02:42.110 --> 00:02:48.340
a Valyrian steel sword. Melisandre says that Azor Ahai will draw the sword from fire. One

00:02:48.340 --> 00:02:53.440
legend about the original Lightbringer says
its creation required the sacrificial execution

00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:59.040
of Azor Ahai’s wife, Nissa Nissa. As Davos
speculates, it might be that Azor Ahai will

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:03.350
have to make some similar sacrifice, but
that’s never said to be part of any prophecy,

00:03:03.350 --> 00:03:08.590
so it might not be important. According to
Melisandre, Aemon, and Benerro, Azor Ahai

00:03:08.590 --> 00:03:13.720
has something to do with dragons. Melisandre specifically says that Azor Ahai is prophesied

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:18.460
“to wake dragons from stone”, which apparently
requires the sacrifice of someone with king’s

00:03:18.460 --> 00:03:23.400
blood. Since she’s the only person claiming this, and she admits that she sometimes misinterprets

00:03:23.400 --> 00:03:28.230
prophecies, it seems possible that Melisandre is wrong about the stone dragons bit. But

00:03:28.230 --> 00:03:33.590
all agree that Azor Ahai is associated with
dragons, so that at least seems pretty solid.

00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:38.460
Aemon implies that Azor Ahai must have Targaryen blood, and the Ghost of High Heart specifies

00:03:38.460 --> 00:03:43.200
the line of Aerys and Rhaella. To quickly
explain that – Ser Barristan says that Aerys

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:47.340
and Rhaella Targaryen married because a woods
witch said that “the prince that was promised

00:03:47.340 --> 00:03:51.650
would be born of their line”. Ser Barristan’s
description of the woods witch matches the

00:03:51.650 --> 00:03:56.250
description of the Ghost of High Heart, the
mysterious old woman encountered by Arya with

00:03:56.250 --> 00:04:00.960
the Brotherhood Without Banners. Not only
are they both very short women who produce

00:04:00.960 --> 00:04:04.440
prophecies, but they are both associated with
the children of the forest, and they both

00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:09.210
were close to someone named Jenny. So they
almost certainly are the same person. And

00:04:09.210 --> 00:04:13.350
the thing is – the Ghost of High Heart has
proven the reliability of her prophecies by

00:04:13.350 --> 00:04:18.130
making a lot of really impressive accurate
predictions. Therefore, Barristan’s woods

00:04:18.130 --> 00:04:22.400
witch, the Ghost of High Heart, is almost
certainly correct in saying that Azor Ahai

00:04:22.400 --> 00:04:29.030
must have the blood of Aerys and Rhaella Targaryen.
A couple more things – both Aemon and Rhaegar

00:04:29.030 --> 00:04:34.370
in a vision say “the dragon must have three
heads”. Some people think this means Azor

00:04:34.370 --> 00:04:38.520
Ahai is three people, but that’s not what
the text suggests. What the three heads of

00:04:38.520 --> 00:04:43.460
the dragon seems to mean is that Azor Ahai should have two companions who help’m out,

00:04:43.460 --> 00:04:47.620
maybe ride dragons with them, whatever.
Aemon says that he could have been one of

00:04:47.620 --> 00:04:52.090
the three heads, if he wasn’t so old. This
means that that the three heads are not special

00:04:52.090 --> 00:04:57.220
prophesied figures, but can probably be any
Targaryen, or anyone at all. The three heads

00:04:57.220 --> 00:05:01.520
of the dragon may be a thing, but it’s not
part of any known prophecy and it does not

00:05:01.520 --> 00:05:07.220
mean three people are Azor Ahai. Finally,
Rhaegar Targaryen, in a vision, says of the

00:05:07.220 --> 00:05:11.540
“prince that was promised” that “His
is the song of ice and fire”. Again, this

00:05:11.540 --> 00:05:15.120
doesn’t seem to be part of any prophecy,
and it’s very vague, but it’s probably

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:19.000
worth keeping in mind.
So. We’ve got seven signs of Azor Ahai.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:24.000
The star, the salt, the smoke, the sword,
the sacrifice, the stone dragons, and the

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:29.010
blood. Azor Ahai is someone from the line
of Aerys and Rhaella Targaryen, someone born

00:05:29.010 --> 00:05:34.040
beneath a bleeding star, and amidst salt and
smoke. They should have a burning sword, and

00:05:34.040 --> 00:05:39.560
have something to do with dragons, maybe awakening
stone dragons. Sacrifice might be involved

00:05:39.560 --> 00:05:43.720
with the stone dragons or with the sword.
The three heads of the dragon and the “song

00:05:43.720 --> 00:05:49.470
of ice and fire” may also be involved somehow.
To find Azor Ahai, we must find the person

00:05:49.470 --> 00:05:54.669
who best fits this description.
Melisandre says that Stannis Baratheon is

00:05:54.669 --> 00:06:00.050
Azor Ahai, and she tries very hard to make
him fit the seven signs. Like every character

00:06:00.050 --> 00:06:04.240
alive during A Clash of Kings, Stannis is
around to see the red comet that appears in

00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:09.010
the sky and is named the “Bleeding Star”
by Dany and the Dothraki. Not long after

00:06:09.010 --> 00:06:13.460
the comet appears is the ceremony at Dragonstone where statues of the Seven are burned and

00:06:13.460 --> 00:06:18.400
Stannis is proclaimed to be Azor Ahai. So
this is a symbolic rebirth, of sorts, which

00:06:18.400 --> 00:06:23.449
happens shortly after, if not under, a “bleeding
star”. It happens amidst salt and smoke

00:06:23.449 --> 00:06:28.270
– the salt of the ocean, the smoke of the
burning gods. So Stannis has the star, smoke

00:06:28.270 --> 00:06:33.710
and salt. At the same ceremony, he draws a
sword from fire, and names it Lightbringer.

00:06:33.710 --> 00:06:38.620
But as Jon points out, the sword’s not warm or hot as Lightbringer should be. Aemon says

00:06:38.620 --> 00:06:42.419
“the sword is wrong”, and describes its
light as an “empty glamor” – perhaps

00:06:42.419 --> 00:06:47.550
what magic it has is another of Melisandre’s
illusions. So as Sallador Saan says, “That

00:06:47.550 --> 00:06:52.000
sword was not Lightbringer” . As for the
sacrifice, Melisandre tries to get Stannis

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:57.040
to sacrifice someone with king’s blood in
order to awaken stone dragons. So far, that

00:06:57.040 --> 00:07:02.169
hasn’t happened – no sacrifice, no dragons.
Stannis does have some Targaryen blood, but

00:07:02.169 --> 00:07:08.180
not from Rhaella and Aerys, so he fails there
too. That’s three out of seven signs. Stannis

00:07:08.180 --> 00:07:11.660
also has no apparent connection to the “song
of ice and fire”, or the three heads of

00:07:11.660 --> 00:07:16.830
the dragon – unless maybe you want to argue
that Stannis, Mel and Davos are three heads,

00:07:16.830 --> 00:07:21.800
whatever than means. So all things considered,
it looks like Stannis is not Azor Ahai. And

00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:25.169
y’know – it wouldn’t fit the story anyway.
Stannis may be the Mannis, but compared to

00:07:25.169 --> 00:07:30.650
people like Dany and Jon, he’s no hero – Stannis
is a harsh, bitter, unromantic man, not a

00:07:30.650 --> 00:07:36.380
save-the-world-with-a-magic-sword kinda guy.
He says as much himself. And come on, what

00:07:36.380 --> 00:07:40.780
kind of champion of R’hllor sets himself
on fire with his own burning sword? The fact

00:07:40.780 --> 00:07:44.840
that we are led to believe that Stannis is
Azor Ahai is a good reason not to believe

00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:49.389
that he is Azor Ahai – why would George
R. R. Martin create all this mystery and prophecy

00:07:49.389 --> 00:07:54.490
only to tell us the answer at the start of
the second book? As George himself has said,

00:07:54.490 --> 00:07:59.210
prophecies should not be too literal and too
easy. Melisandre has tried and failed to

00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:04.620
make Stannis literally fulfil the Azor Ahai
prophecy. As Aemon says, she has misread the

00:08:04.620 --> 00:08:09.419
signs, she is deceiving herself because she
wants to believe. The evidence strongly suggests

00:08:09.419 --> 00:08:16.419
that Stannis Baratheon is not Azor Ahai.
Aemon and Benerro both say that Daenerys Targaryen

00:08:17.060 --> 00:08:22.100
is Azor Ahai . In the final chapter of Book
1, Daenerys sees the “Bleeding Star” appear,

00:08:22.100 --> 00:08:27.520
walks into flames and, amidst smoke, is
reborn as the mother of dragons, “stone

00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:32.839
dragons” which she wakes from eggs. So straight
away that perfectly fits the star, smoke and

00:08:32.839 --> 00:08:38.140
stone dragons. The salt probably comes from
salty smoky Dragonstone, where Dany was literally

00:08:38.140 --> 00:08:43.320
born, if not from tears or sweat at the pyre.
What about Lightbringer? You can argue that

00:08:43.320 --> 00:08:48.430
Dany’s dragons are her fiery weapon. This
is supported by Xaro Xhoan Daxos’ description

00:08:48.430 --> 00:08:52.860
of Dany’s dragons as a “flaming sword”. And when you think about it, Azor Ahai saving

00:08:52.860 --> 00:08:57.480
the world with dragons is a lot more believable
than saving the world with one flaming sword

00:08:57.480 --> 00:09:01.899
– right? Aemon says translation errors are
a problem with this prophecy – thinking that

00:09:01.899 --> 00:09:06.120
Lightbringer is a literal sword might be one
of them. The awakening of the stone dragons,

00:09:06.120 --> 00:09:11.940
the creation of Dany’s burning sword, requires
two sacrifices – of Dany’s love, Drogo,

00:09:11.940 --> 00:09:17.050
and of her stillborn son, Rhaego, who has
the blood of Targaryen kings through Dany.

00:09:17.050 --> 00:09:21.380
We know these deaths are related to birth
of Dany's dragons because, as Dany reminds us

00:09:21.380 --> 00:09:26.399
in the same chapter, “Only death can pay
for life”. So this satisfies both kinds

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:31.000
of sacrifice – of a loved one, for a burning
sword, like Nissa Nissa, and of king’s blood,

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:35.850
to awaken stone dragons, as Mel prophesies.
So we’ve got the sacrifice, the sword, the

00:09:35.850 --> 00:09:40.040
stone dragons, the star, the smoke, the salt,
and we’ve got the blood, because Daenerys

00:09:40.040 --> 00:09:45.810
is the daughter of Aerys and Rhaella Targaryen.
That’s all seven signs, only the sword is

00:09:45.810 --> 00:09:50.170
really questionable. The three heads of the
dragon might relate to Dany’s three dragons

00:09:50.170 --> 00:09:54.350
– three dragon-riders, maybe. She has no
clear connection to the “song of ice and

00:09:54.350 --> 00:09:59.130
fire”, but again the song and heads are
vague and not part of prophecy anyway, so Daenerys

00:09:59.130 --> 00:10:05.140
Targaryen fits everything we reliably know
about Azor Ahai, and has both Aemon and Benerro

00:10:05.140 --> 00:10:10.620
backing her. It also fits the story for Dany
to be Azor Ahai. I mean, come on, she is “Daenerys

00:10:10.620 --> 00:10:16.079
Stormborn”, “the widow of a Dothraki khal,
a mother of dragons and a sacker of cities”,

00:10:16.079 --> 00:10:19.600
she is “the Unburnt”, she is the “Breaker
of Chains”, the “Queen of Meereen,

00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:23.240
Queen of the Andals and the Rhoynar and the
First Men”, “Lord of the Seven Kingdoms”,

00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:26.000
“The fairest woman in the world” , she
is “strong”, she is “fierce” , “the

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:31.120
fire is [hers]”... Don’t know how to put
this, but she’s “kind of a big deal”.

00:10:31.120 --> 00:10:35.080
George R. R. Martin has hyped up Dany all
series, so if anyone’s gonna be the prophesied

00:10:35.080 --> 00:10:40.050
saviour of the world, it’ll be her. She
has the signs, it fits the story, Dany is

00:10:40.050 --> 00:10:44.330
probably Azor Ahai.
But there’s another strong candidate. Jon

00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:49.060
Snow might be Azor Ahai. Of course, last we heard from him he’d been stabbed four times,

00:10:49.060 --> 00:10:53.270
but he could be resurrected by Melisandre
– we know red priests can do this from Beric

00:10:53.270 --> 00:10:58.290
Dondarrion and Thoros of Myr. There’s evidence
that Jon might warg into his direwolf Ghost

00:10:58.290 --> 00:11:02.770
before returning to his body. We know wargs
can do this, and that Jon is unknowingly a

00:11:02.770 --> 00:11:07.300
powerful warg, from the Dance with Dragons Prologue. The idea is supported by a vision

00:11:07.300 --> 00:11:12.339
that Melisandre has of Jon, in which he changes from a man, to a wolf, to a man again. Further,

00:11:12.339 --> 00:11:18.230
Jon’s last word after being stabbed is “Ghost”. All this suggests that Jon will warg into

00:11:18.230 --> 00:11:23.500
Ghost, then be reborn – a man once more.
Now look at the passage where Jon is stabbed

00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:29.110
– Jon’s wound is smoking, Bowen Marsh
is crying salty tears, and Ser Patrick, whose

00:11:29.110 --> 00:11:35.510
"distinctive" heraldry features stars, is bleeding.
A lot. Each of these things is emphasised

00:11:35.510 --> 00:11:40.839
right at Jon’s stabbing. The star, the smoke, the salt. And Jon brings up the “promised

00:11:40.839 --> 00:11:45.690
prince, born in smoke and salt” in the same
chapter as the stabbing. The star is a bit

00:11:45.690 --> 00:11:50.149
dodgy, but can this really be a coincidence?
Let’s look at the other signs. Jon does

00:11:50.149 --> 00:11:55.180
have a pretty sweet sword, a Valyrian steel sword, but hardly Lightbringer. You could argue that

00:11:55.180 --> 00:11:59.149
the Night’s Watch is his fiery weapon – their
vow says “I am the sword in the darkness”,

00:11:59.149 --> 00:12:03.420
and they’re a weapon against the Others,
and Jon kinda sacrificed his love Ygritte

00:12:03.420 --> 00:12:09.500
for them. So, maybe. But, again, it may be
that the sign of the sword is a mistranslation

00:12:09.500 --> 00:12:14.170
or misinterpretation of the sign of the dragons,
in which case Jon might need one of Dany’s

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:19.149
dragons. Alternatively, Jon might wake a dragon from stone by discovering

00:12:19.149 --> 00:12:23.450
his Targaryen parentage in the Winterfell
crypts – there are some cool theories about

00:12:23.450 --> 00:12:30.450
Rhaegar’s harp that could help here. Another is waking a dragon from within the Wall. But both of these are just future speculation. 

00:12:30.450 --> 00:12:33.410
For now, Jon has no dragon, probably no sword,

00:12:33.420 --> 00:12:37.760
and probably no sacrifice, but these are things
that could happen later. We’ve still got

00:12:37.760 --> 00:12:44.160
two books coming. Now, if R+L=J is true, and
it very probably is, Jon has the blood. That

00:12:44.160 --> 00:12:47.920
would also literally make him the “prince
that was promised” and would make him of

00:12:47.920 --> 00:12:53.640
ice and fire. So Jon satisfies most of the
signs of Azor Ahai. Less than Dany. But there’s

00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:58.160
strong additional evidence that Jon is Azor
Ahai. Melisandre says that when she tries

00:12:58.160 --> 00:13:03.910
to see Azor Ahai in her flames, R’hllor
shows her Snow, as in Jon Snow. This happens

00:13:03.910 --> 00:13:08.570
repeatedly. Must be pretty frustrating for
R’hllor, that Melisandre never makes the

00:13:08.570 --> 00:13:13.430
connection, right? Also, Jon has a dream in
which he wields a burning red sword against

00:13:13.430 --> 00:13:18.310
the Others, at the Wall. He shouts about fire,
and even slays the woman he loves with the

00:13:18.310 --> 00:13:23.149
red sword. These are some pretty strong hints, right? So there’s a lot of evidence suggesting

00:13:23.149 --> 00:13:28.320
that Jon Snow is Azor Ahai. And it would make
narrative sense too. Jon clearly is someone

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:32.850
special, as indicated by his white direwolf
and even his bastardy, which has always marked

00:13:32.850 --> 00:13:37.540
him as someone who is different. He’s a
heroic figure, brave, honourable, determined

00:13:37.540 --> 00:13:41.510
to do what’s right. And he’s already
fighting the Others, which is what Azor Ahai

00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:47.000
does. It makes a lot of sense for Jon
to be Azor Ahai.

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:53.769
So. Stannis is probably not Azor Ahai. The evidence
points to Dany… and also to Jon. Looks like

00:13:53.769 --> 00:13:58.800
they’re both Azor Ahai. The "song of ice
and fire", right? But let’s look at other possibilities.

00:13:58.800 --> 00:14:01.769
Could there be a third Azor Ahai? Aegon, if

00:14:01.769 --> 00:14:07.130
he really is Aegon, has the blood, and apparently
the star. Rhaegar also had the blood, and

00:14:07.130 --> 00:14:12.560
was born amidst salt and smoke. Victarion
has a burned, smoking hand. Davos was reborn

00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:17.160
amidst salt and smoke. The Lightning Lord
has a burning sword, Brienne has a red sword.

00:14:17.160 --> 00:14:21.860
Tyrion makes a nice trio with Dany and Jon.
Ramsay has the name Snow. Jamie could Nissa

00:14:21.860 --> 00:14:27.269
Nissa Cersei, J-bear could Nissa Nissa Dany,
Hot Pie bakes salty pies in smoky ovens, and

00:14:27.269 --> 00:14:34.269
Pretty Pig is- is ham. You can find some connections
and possibilities for almost any character,

00:14:34.390 --> 00:14:39.600
but only Dany and Jon are strongly supported
by evidence. Only Dany and Jon have

00:14:39.600 --> 00:14:44.450
important signs like the blood, the star,
salt and smoke. Only Dany and Jon have heaps

00:14:44.450 --> 00:14:48.959
of foreshadowing, hints and visions. It would
be bad storytelling to spend the whole series

00:14:48.959 --> 00:14:55.959
focussing on Dany and Jon before going ‘heyy, by the way, this guy- this guy Aegon, or this guy, fuckin',

00:14:55.990 --> 00:15:00.220
Ramsay Snow, he’s also a saviour of the
world!’ It would also ruin the nice little

00:15:00.220 --> 00:15:05.430
Song of Ice and Fire we’ve got going with
Jon and Dany. So a third Azor Ahai is not

00:15:05.430 --> 00:15:10.050
impossible, but it seems unlikely and there’s really no good reason to believe it.

00:15:10.050 --> 00:15:15.190
Another argument you can make is that no one
is Azor Ahai. The prophecy is wrong or irrelevant.

00:15:15.190 --> 00:15:19.579
But it would be even worse than a third Azor
Ahai to build up all this foreshadowing, all

00:15:19.579 --> 00:15:24.100
these visions and hints, and then throw’em away and say they mean nothing. Azor Ahai

00:15:24.100 --> 00:15:28.110
doesn’t have to be a perfect fairy tale
hero who makes everything better. We know

00:15:28.110 --> 00:15:32.139
prophecy’s a bitch, we know things are complicated
– but with all this evidence, Azor Ahai

00:15:32.139 --> 00:15:35.990
has to mean something.
There are other objections and convoluted

00:15:35.990 --> 00:15:41.100
complications that you could raise. But everything
we currently know about Azor Ahai points to

00:15:41.100 --> 00:15:47.019
two people – Jon and Dany. Dany fits the
prophecy almost perfectly, Jon fits most of

00:15:47.019 --> 00:15:52.200
it and has extra hints on top. Jon and Dany
are the two main characters, together representing

00:15:52.200 --> 00:15:57.790
ice and fire, the title of the series. Based
on what we now know, the most reasonable conclusion

00:15:57.790 --> 00:16:02.920
to come to is that Dany and Jon are Azor Ahai,
and are prophesied to save the world from

00:16:02.980 --> 00:16:06.000
a night that never ends.

00:16:06.060 --> 00:16:09.180
Thanks for watching. Subscribe if you'd like to see more.

